title: Judge dismisses Elon Musk's suit against hate speech researchers
description: The billionaire sued the Center for Countering Digital Hate after the group published a series of reports detailing an uptick of hate speech on X, the platform formerly known as Twitter.

title: Hurry up and wait: Servers speed-walk through Paris, reviving a century-old race
description: Some 200 servers speed-walked through Paris balancing trays of beverages and croissants on Sunday. Paris hasn't held a waiters race since 2011, but brought it back ahead of the Olympics.

title: Boeing CEO Dave Calhoun to step down, part of a shakeup after 737 Max problems
description: After several difficult months, Boeing announced its embattled chief executive will step down at the end of this year. In January, an Alaska Airlines 737 Max had an in-flight door plug blowout.

title: Photos: See D.C.'s cherry blossoms in peak bloom, bid farewell to 'Stumpy'
description: Later this spring, 158 of the cherry blossom trees will be cut down as part of a project to rebuild and raise the seawalls around the Tidal Basin.

title: How to talk to kids about a cancer diagnosis in the family
description: Kate Middleton said she took time to explain her cancer diagnosis to her children. What does an ideal version of that conversation look like?

title: New England and New York dig out as a new storm will bring snow to the Midwest
description: Police across the Northeast reported hundreds of traffic accidents over the weekend. Meanwhile, a separate storm will continue Monday across much of the Rockies, Plains and upper Midwest.
